The paper discusses the design of next-generation optical access networks, which involves topics related to networking, communication, and information theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the energy efficiency of the proposed architectures, which falls under the sub-category cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the Quality of Experience (QoE) of the proposed architectures, which falls under the sub-category cs.COMM (Computer Communication and Networks). The paper also discusses the implementation of a virtual test bed, which involves topics related to computer architecture and programming, falling under the sub-category cs.AR (Architecture). Finally, the paper discusses the development of a comparison framework based on statistical hypothesis testing, which falls under the sub-category cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
